 class=m><span class=title> Four simple Rules to keep YOU from being scammed:</span><hr size=1> 1) Don't ever make a trade without getting back exactly what you want in that same trade. i.e. Don't trade the FBSS to Joe then wait while Joe gets John to trade you the Lammy. Don't let the fact that you really want the Lammy cloud your judgement.<br>
<br>
2) Don't even put something in the trade window with a character of such low level that there is nothing to lose in deleting the character. Make sure you know the class and level of characters you trade with, even if it means having them take anon and RP off. If they say they are a trademule then have them log in their main character for a min to prove their identity.<br>
<br>
3) Never initiate a trade with a person obstructed in any way by zone or prop geometry or who is moving around. ie don't trade with people in firepots. Sometimes its worth it to initiate all trades with 1cp and then drop items into the trade window and not onto the character pixels. <br>
<br>
4) Never auction that you are looking to buy an uber item. Most scammers never even have the item you are looking for. But they know that your desire for finally obtaining the uber item of your dreams will cloud your judgement.<br>
<br>
Good luck<br>
<br>
G<br>
